📘 Spring Boot – Simple Web Controller Project
This is a small Spring Boot project demonstrating how a Controller works inside a Spring Boot application and how component scanning detects classes inside sub‑packages.

🏗️ Project Structure
Code
src/main/java/com/shaktihazaru/www
│
├── SampleWebApplication.java   ← Main Spring Boot class
│
└── controller
    └── HomeController.java     ← Handles /msg endpoint
🚀 How the Application Starts
Spring Boot applications always start from the class annotated with:

SpringBootApplication

A main() method

In this project, that class is:

Code
com.shaktihazaru.www.SampleWebApplication
This class:

Starts the Spring Boot framework

Starts the embedded Tomcat server

Performs component scanning

Loads all controllers, services, repositories

You cannot run a controller directly because controllers do not contain a main() method or server startup logic.

🧩 Component Scanning (Why Your Controller Works)
Spring Boot automatically scans all sub‑packages under the package where the main class is located.

Main class package:

Code
com.shaktihazaru.www
Controller package:

Code
com.shaktihazaru.www.controller
Since controller is a child package, Spring Boot automatically detects HomeController.

🧭 HomeController Explained
java
@RestController
public class HomeController {

    @RequestMapping("/msg")
    public String message() {
        return "Krishna is the Supreme Personality of Godhead";
    }
}
✔ @RestController
Tells Spring this class handles web requests and returns data directly.

✔ @RequestMapping("/msg")
Maps the URL /msg to the message() method.

✔ Return value
Because of @RestController, the returned string becomes the HTTP response body.

🌐 How to Access the Endpoint
Start the application by running:

Code
SampleWebApplication
Then open your browser:

Code
http://localhost:8080/msg
You will see:

Code
Krishna is the Supreme Personality of Godhead
🧠 Why You Cannot “Run” HomeController
Controllers are not runnable classes.
They:

Have no main() method

Do not start the server

Only respond to HTTP requests after the Spring Boot app is running

Only the main class (SampleWebApplication) can start the application.

📌 Summary
Spring Boot starts from the main class (SampleWebApplication)

Controllers are discovered through component scanning

You cannot run a controller directly

The /msg endpoint works once the app is running

@RestController returns plain text or JSON directly
